African Rugby announced it would be parting ways with the Springbok coach
Allister Coetzee with immediate effect. According
to Sports24, Coetzee and SA Rugby
agreed to terminate the relationship after a two-year association. Although
the sudden news of Coetzee’s sacking shocked sports fans, others were pleased
with the decision and expressed their satisfaction on Twitter.    What are your thoughts on Coetzee being fired? Was it about time or should they have given him a bit more time? 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  